  "description": "Analysis Shows We\u0026rsquo;ll Pass 1.5c in Months (description:: Current El Nino almost certain to push Earth past the crucial 1.5°C warming threshold)\nA new study by James Hansen and his colleagues at NASA\u0026rsquo;s Goddard Institute for Space Studies has found that global warming is accelerating at an alarming rate. The study, published in the journal Environmental Research Letters, shows that the Earth\u0026rsquo;s energy imbalance, the main driver of warming, has doubled in the past decade. This is causing global temperatures to rise at a rate of nearly 0.5°C per decade, which is more than twice the rate observed from 1970 to 2010.\n",
